ne**: add `controller.enqueue(encoder.encode(\":\\n\\n\"));` at the top of `start(controller)`. All existing unit tests continue to pass unchanged.\n- **Lint**: 4 pre-existing `noExplicitAny` warnings in `src/lib/__tests__/seed.test.ts` — none introduced by F17.\n- **Integration gap (known)**: full end-to-end streaming test (connect SSE → POST event → assert event appears in stream) requires both ClickHouse and the dev server; not attempted here.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WFCYVj3u82BkrJ9z46cLHg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**F17 Eval Sprint 1 — complete.**\n\n## Summary\n\n**Score: 7/10 — NEEDS_WORK**\n\nAll Phase A checks pass cleanly:\n- Tests: 259 passed, 0 failures\n- Lint: exit 0 (4 pre-existing warnings in `seed.test.ts`, none new)\n- Typecheck: exit 0\n- Build: exit 0, `/api/live` registered as dynamic route\n\n**Phase B (HTTP check) fails:** `GET /api/live` returns 0 bytes — the client never receives response headers.\n\n**Root cause:** `new Response(stream, { headers })` in Next.js App Router does not flush the HTTP status line and headers until the first byte of the body is written. The `ReadableStream` only enqueues data when ClickHouse returns events. When ClickHouse is unavailable (or returns empty results), nothing is enqueued and the client hangs indefinitely.\n\nThis affects both dev and production mode. The unit tests all pass because they call `GET()` in-process and inspect the `Response` object — they never exercise the HTTP serialization path.\n\n**Fix (one line):** add `controller.enqueue(encoder.encode(\":\\n\\n\"));` at the top of the `start(controller)` callback in `src/app/api/live/route.ts:26`, before `setInterval`. SSE clients treat `:` lines as comments and discard them; this is the standard pattern for immediately flushing headers on connect."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2602,"cache_read_input_tokens":59492,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2602},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5aaa11d-67a7-4ffc-9b3b-2cb42566b1cb","uuid":"7f5255fb-cf21-494d-96b0-46a7607fdb63"}
